Job Description
•Assist the VP/GM in quarterly and yearly strategic planning as well as review periodical metrics and develop action plans to address issues in the business
•Conduct research and analysis on industry trends, competitive developments, products and customers. Consult with Management on both practical and innovative solytions with the end objective of supporting organizational growth
•Participate in business performance review and analysis, preparation of reports, proposals and presentation materials
•Collaborate and assist Sales and Business Managers to support business development or sales improvement activities
•Assist in analyzing organizational effectiveness, propose and implement improvement plans for the Business Unit to enhance sustainable business development
•Participate in the Emerson periodic business planning process
Job Requirements
Minimum 2-3 years of working experience in the following: i.Sales ii.Business Development iii.Market Research & Analysis iv.Business Consultancy
Soft Skills
i.Excellent interpersonal and organizational skills with a stroing commitment to excel
ii.Pleasant personality with ability to work with individuals of different levels in the organization
iii.Possess a high degree of professionalism and integrity
Professional / Technical Competencies
i.Ability to understand the budgeting process as well as analyzing the financial statements of the company ii.Keep abreast with the trend, technologies and changes in the business landscape of the industry iii.Analytical with strong research, problem solving and presentation skills
